This folder  contains an integrated bioinformatics workflow covering sequence similarity search, multiple sequence alignment, and phylogenetic analysis. The pipeline is used to study evolutionary relationships and support structural bioinformatics investigations.

📁 Folder Structure
BLAST_Analysis/
Identification of homologous sequences using NCBI BLAST to find similar sequences in public databases.
Multiple_Sequence_Alignment/
Alignment of selected sequences to detect conserved regions, mutations, and functional motifs.
Phylogenetic_Analysis/
Construction of phylogenetic trees to analyze evolutionary relationships among related sequences.
🔄 Workflow

BLAST → Multiple Sequence Alignment → Phylogenetic Tree Construction

-Retrieve homologous sequences using BLAST
-Perform multiple sequence alignment on selected sequences
-Build phylogenetic tree to study evolutionary relationships

##🛠 Tools Used
-NCBI BLAST
-MEGA 11 / Clustal Omega / MUSCLE
-Phylogenetic analysis tools (MEGA or similar software)
-FASTA sequence format

##🎯 Objective

This workflow helps in:

-Identifying sequence similarity across species
-Detecting conserved and variable regions
-Understanding evolutionary relationships
-Supporting downstream structural and functional analysis
##📌 Project Type

Bioinformatics | Structural Analysis | Evolutionary Study
